1
00:00:27,093 --> 00:00:30,096
TOMMY, HIT IT UP !
LET'S HAVE IT !

2
00:00:30,096 --> 00:00:35,101
♪

3
00:00:48,114 --> 00:00:50,616
MAY I CUT IN ?
WHY, CERTAINLY.

4
00:00:55,622 --> 00:00:58,124
BOYS WILL BE BOYS.
WHOO !

5
00:01:09,636 --> 00:01:12,639
NOT ALL GIRLS ARE RAVING
BLOODY LESBIANS, YOU KNOW.

6
00:01:12,639 --> 00:01:16,142
THAT IS A MISFORTUNE
THAT I'M PERFECTLY WELL AWARE OF.

7
00:01:23,149 --> 00:01:27,153
SHE SAYS THAT I THINK MORE
OF YOU THAN I DO OF HER.

8
00:01:30,156 --> 00:01:32,658
WELL, YOU DO,
DON'T YOU ?

9
00:01:32,659 --> 00:01:34,160
WELL, WE WON'T
GO INTO THAT.

10
00:01:34,661 --> 00:01:36,663
OH !

11
00:01:37,664 --> 00:01:39,666
GO RIGHT AHEAD, BOYS.
DON'T MIND ME.

12
00:01:46,673 --> 00:01:48,675
BUT YOU'RE NOT A GIRL,
YOU'RE A GUY, AND WHY WOULD A GUY...

13
00:01:48,675 --> 00:01:51,678
WANT TO MARRY A GUY ?
SECURITY.

14
00:01:51,678 --> 00:01:56,182
I THINK THAT THE RIGHT WOMAN
COULD REFORM YOU.

15
00:01:56,182 --> 00:01:59,685
YOU KNOW, I THINK THE RIGHT
WOMAN COULD REFORM YOU TOO. OH !

16
00:01:59,686 --> 00:02:04,190
THESE AREN'T MY CLOTHES.
WHY ARE YOU WEARING THESE CLOTHES ?

17
00:02:04,190 --> 00:02:07,193
BECAUSE I JUST WENT GAY
ALL OF A SUDDEN !

18
00:02:38,224 --> 00:02:40,226
[ Lily Tomlin ]
IN A HUNDRED YEARS OF MOVIES,

19
00:02:40,226 --> 00:02:44,730
HOMOSEXUALITY HAS ONLY RARELY
BEEN DEPICTED ON THE SCREEN.

20
00:02:46,232 --> 00:02:49,735
WHEN IT DID APPEAR, IT WAS THERE
AS SOMETHING TO LAUGH AT...

21
00:02:49,736 --> 00:02:52,739
OR SOMETHING TO PITY,

22
00:02:54,741 --> 00:02:57,243
OR EVEN SOMETHING TO FEAR.

23
00:03:00,747 --> 00:03:04,250
THESE WERE FLEETING IMAGES,
BUT THEY WERE UNFORGETTABLE.

24
00:03:04,751 --> 00:03:07,253
AND THEY LEFT A LASTING LEGACY.

25
00:03:09,756 --> 00:03:13,760
HOLLYWOOD,
THAT GREAT MAKER OF MYTHS, TAUGHT STRAIGHT PEOPLE...

26
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:16,763
WHAT TO THINK
ABOUT GAY PEOPLE...

27
00:03:16,763 --> 00:03:21,267
AND GAY PEOPLE WHAT TO THINK
ABOUT THEMSELVES.

28
00:03:21,267 --> 00:03:24,270
NO ONE ESCAPED ITS INFLUENCE.

29
00:03:25,271 --> 00:03:27,773
MOVIES ARE PART
OF MY LIFE.

30
00:03:27,774 --> 00:03:29,776
PART OF
EVERYBODY'S LIFE.

31
00:03:29,776 --> 00:03:31,778
THAT'S WHERE
WE LEARN ABOUT LIFE.

32
00:03:31,778 --> 00:03:34,781
WATCHING CARY GRANT TAUGHT ME
HOW TO BEHAVE WITH A WOMAN,

33
00:03:34,781 --> 00:03:36,783
HOW TO GET DRESSED AT NIGHT,

34
00:03:36,783 --> 00:03:39,786
HOW TO GO TO A RESTAURANT
AND ORDER DINNER.

35
00:03:39,786 --> 00:03:43,289
THEY'RE OUR STORYTELLING.
THEY'RE THE FABRIC OF OUR LIVES.

36
00:03:43,289 --> 00:03:47,793
THEY SHOW US WHAT IS GLORIOUS...

37
00:03:47,794 --> 00:03:51,297
AND TRAGIC AND WONDERFUL
AND FUNNY...

38
00:03:51,297 --> 00:03:55,301
ABOUT THE DAY-TO-DAY EXPERIENCES
THAT WE ALL SHARE.

39
00:03:55,301 --> 00:04:00,306
AND WHEN YOU'RE GAY AND DON'T
SEE THAT REFLECTED IN ANY WAY,

40
00:04:00,306 --> 00:04:02,308
EVER,
IN THE MOVIES,

41
00:04:02,308 --> 00:04:05,811
YOU BEGAN TO FEEL
THAT SOMETHING TRULY IS WRONG.

42
00:04:05,812 --> 00:04:09,816
YOU FEEL INVISIBLE; YOU FEEL
LIKE A GHOST,

43
00:04:09,816 --> 00:04:12,819
AND A GHOST THAT NOBODY
BELIEVES IN.

44
00:04:12,819 --> 00:04:15,321
THERE'S THIS SENSE
OF ISOLATION.

45
00:04:15,321 --> 00:04:17,323
JOIN THE CLUB,
MAN.

46
00:04:17,323 --> 00:04:20,826
[ Laughs ]
THIS IS A WHOLE GROUP,

47
00:04:20,827 --> 00:04:23,329
YOU KNOW,
THAT IS NOT REPRESENTED.

48
00:04:23,329 --> 00:04:26,832
WE ARE PATHETICALLY STARVED
FOR IMAGES OF OURSELVES.

49
00:04:26,833 --> 00:04:29,335
SO MUCH SO THAT A FRIEND
WILL CALL YOU UP AND SAY,

50
00:04:29,335 --> 00:04:32,338
"OH, THERE'S A MOVIE YOU MUST
SEE !"  THIS HAPPENED TO ME.

51
00:04:32,338 --> 00:04:36,342
"THIS MOVIE YOU'VE GOTTA SEE.
THERE'S THIS INCREDIBLE LESBIAN RELATIONSHIP IN IT.

52
00:04:36,342 --> 00:04:38,344
"AND THERE'S THIS GREAT
LOVE SCENE, AND--

53
00:04:38,344 --> 00:04:42,348
ALL RIGHT, THEY'RE VAMPIRES;
BUT YOU GOTTA SEE IT. IT'S GREAT."

54
00:04:42,348 --> 00:04:45,351
THERE ARE LOTS OF NEEDS
FOR ART.

55
00:04:45,351 --> 00:04:48,354
THE GREATEST ONE IS THE MIRROR
OF OUR OWN LIVES...

56
00:04:48,354 --> 00:04:51,357
AND OUR OWN EXISTENCE.

57
00:04:51,357 --> 00:04:53,859
AND THAT HUNGER
THAT I FELT AS A KID,

58
00:04:53,860 --> 00:04:57,864
LOOKING FOR GAY IMAGES,
WAS TO NOT BE ALONE.

59
00:05:16,883 --> 00:05:19,385
MY MOTHER TOOK ME
TO THE SILENT MOVIES...

60
00:05:19,886 --> 00:05:23,389
IN A SPIRIT
OF OSTENTATIOUS CONDESCENSION.

61
00:05:23,389 --> 00:05:28,394
SHE TOLD ME THAT THEY
WERE NOTHING LIKE REAL LIFE...

62
00:05:28,394 --> 00:05:30,896
AND THAT I MUST NOT
BELIEVE THEM.

63
00:05:30,897 --> 00:05:33,399
AND SHE WAS WRONG,
BECAUSE EVERYONE...

64
00:05:33,399 --> 00:05:36,902
WHO COMES FROM ENGLAND
TO AMERICA AND GOES BACK...

65
00:05:36,903 --> 00:05:39,405
SAYS ONE THING FIRST.

66
00:05:39,405 --> 00:05:43,409
"IT'S MORE LIKE THE MOVIES
THAN YOU'D EVER DREAM."

67
00:05:43,409 --> 00:05:45,411
AND IT IS.

68
00:05:51,918 --> 00:05:55,421
[ Tomlin ]
FROM THE VERY BEGINNING, MOVIES COULD RELY ON HOMOSEXUALITY...

69
00:05:55,421 --> 00:05:58,424
AS A SUREFIRE SOURCE OF HUMOR.

70
00:06:20,947 --> 00:06:25,451
YOUR IDEAS ABOUT WHO YOU ARE
DON'T JUST COME FROM INSIDE YOU, THEY COME FROM THE CULTURE.

71
00:06:25,952 --> 00:06:29,455
AND IN THIS CULTURE THEY COME
ESPECIALLY FROM THE MOVIES.

72
00:06:29,455 --> 00:06:34,460
SO WE LEARN WHAT IT MEANS
TO BE A MAN OR A WOMAN, TO HAVE SEXUALITY.

73
00:06:43,469 --> 00:06:46,972
[ Dyer ]
THE MOVIES DID PROVIDE US WITH SOME KIND OF HISTORY...

74
00:06:47,473 --> 00:06:50,476
OF HOW SOCIETY
THOUGHT HOMOSEXUALS WERE.

75
00:06:56,482 --> 00:06:59,985
A VERY GOOD EXAMPLE IS THE
CHAPLIN FILM BEHIND THE SCREEN.

76
00:06:59,986 --> 00:07:03,990
THERE IS AN EXTRAORDINARY MOMENT
WHERE CHAPLIN KISSES SOMEONE WHO LOOKS LIKE A MAN.

77
00:07:03,990 --> 00:07:06,492
HE KNOWS THAT IT'S A WOMAN.

78
00:07:06,492 --> 00:07:10,496
AND SOMEONE ELSE COMES ALONG
AND SEES IT AND IMMEDIATELY STARTS SWISHING AROUND...

79
00:07:10,496 --> 00:07:13,999
IN THE MOST KIND OF OVERT,
EFFEMINATE WAY.

80
00:07:25,011 --> 00:07:29,015
IT'S FASCINATING
THAT THOSE STEREOTYPES WERE SO COMPLETELY IN PLACE...

81
00:07:29,515 --> 00:07:33,018
THAT A, YOU KNOW, MAINSTREAM
POPULAR FILM COULD ASSUME...

82
00:07:33,019 --> 00:07:36,522
THAT THE AUDIENCE WOULD KNOW
WHAT THIS SWISHY MIME WAS ALL ABOUT.

83
00:07:41,027 --> 00:07:44,530
- MR. ERNEST.
- ERNEST.

84
00:07:44,530 --> 00:07:48,033
DEAR ERNEST !

85
00:07:48,034 --> 00:07:52,538
DEAR LADY GRAYSTON.
ERNEST, I'M SO HAPPY YOU WERE ABLE TO COME.

86
00:07:52,538 --> 00:07:55,040
YOU MUST EXCUSE MY COMING
IN MY TOWN CLOTHES,

87
00:07:55,041 --> 00:07:59,045
BUT THERE WASN'T A MOMENT
TO LOSE, SO I CAME JUST AS I AM.

88
00:07:59,045 --> 00:08:01,547
[ Tomlin ]
ENTER THE SISSY,

89
00:08:01,547 --> 00:08:03,549
HOLLYWOOD'S FIRST GAY
STOCK CHARACTER.

90
00:08:09,055 --> 00:08:12,558
THE SISSY MADE EVERYONE
FEEL MORE MANLY OR MORE WOMANLY...

91
00:08:12,558 --> 00:08:15,561
BY OCCUPYING THE SPACE
IN BETWEEN.

92
00:08:17,063 --> 00:08:19,065
HE DIDN'T SEEM TO HAVE
A SEXUALITY,

93
00:08:19,065 --> 00:08:22,068
SO HOLLYWOOD ALLOWED HIM
TO THRIVE.

94
00:08:22,068 --> 00:08:26,072
[ Woman ]
THEY WERE SISSIES, NEVER ADDRESSED AS HOMOSEXUAL.

95
00:08:26,072 --> 00:08:28,074
IT WAS A CONVENTION
THAT WAS ACCEPTED.

96
00:08:28,074 --> 00:08:33,079
THEY WERE PERCEIVED AS
HOMOSEXUALS JUST SUBLIMINALLY.

97
00:08:33,079 --> 00:08:38,084
THIS IS A SUBJECT THAT
WAS <i>NOT</i> DISCUSSED PRIVATELY.

98
00:08:38,084 --> 00:08:40,586
UH, CERTAINLY NOT PUBLICLY.

99
00:08:40,586 --> 00:08:43,589
IT WASN'T DISCUSSED,
BUT YOU KNEW.

100
00:08:43,589 --> 00:08:46,091
THEY WERE ALL VERY PRISSY.

101
00:08:46,092 --> 00:08:50,596
YOU KNOW, THESE LITTLE SKINNY
WHITE MEN WITH LITTLE MOUSTACHES WHO WOULD GO LIKE THIS.

102
00:08:50,596 --> 00:08:54,600
[ Women Chattering ]
GIRLS !  GIRLS !

103
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:57,603
BE CAREFUL OF MY HATS !
WE GOTTA GET ON THE STAGE !

104
00:08:57,603 --> 00:09:00,105
I DON'T CARE !  I WON'T
ALLOW YOU TO RUIN THEM.

105
00:09:00,106 --> 00:09:02,608
I TOLD YOU THEY WERE TOO HIGH
AND TOO WIDE.

106
00:09:03,109 --> 00:09:07,113
WELL, BIG WOMAN,
I DESIGN THE COSTUMES,

107
00:09:07,113 --> 00:09:09,115
NOT THE DOORS
FOR THE THEATER.

108
00:09:09,115 --> 00:09:12,118
IF YOU HAD,
THEY'D HAVE BEEN LAVENDER. HMPH !

109
00:09:13,619 --> 00:09:16,622
THIS IS RIPPED.
WHO WERE YOU WITH LAST NIGHT ?

110
00:09:16,622 --> 00:09:20,125
STRANGLER LEWIS.
OH !  CATCH AS CATCH CAN, HMM ?

111
00:09:20,126 --> 00:09:25,131
IF WE COULD GET THE RUNS
WITH THIS SHOW THAT THESE DAMES GET IN THEIR STOCKINGS,

112
00:09:25,131 --> 00:09:28,634
I'D BE ABLE TO MAKE
THE SECOND PAYMENT ON MY KIMONO !

113
00:09:28,634 --> 00:09:32,137
HERE, CLARENCE.
PUT THAT IN THE TRUNK.

114
00:09:32,138 --> 00:09:34,140
AND DON'T WEAR IT.

115
00:09:35,641 --> 00:09:37,643
SELFISH.

116
00:09:37,643 --> 00:09:42,147
THEY WERE A CLICHE. I DON'T CARE
WHETHER THEY WERE A GAY CLICHE OR WHAT.

117
00:09:42,148 --> 00:09:45,151
I THOUGHT THEY WERE DISGUSTING,

118
00:09:45,151 --> 00:09:48,654
UNFUNNY, HAD NO BUSINESS
BEING IN IT.

119
00:09:48,654 --> 00:09:52,157
AND I NEVER UNDERSTOOD
WHY PEOPLE LAUGHED.

120
00:09:54,160 --> 00:09:58,164
IT'S THE SAME THING WHEN THEY
HAD THE STEPPIN FETCHITS FOR THE BLACKS.

121
00:09:58,164 --> 00:10:00,666
I LIKE THE SISSY.

122
00:10:00,666 --> 00:10:05,170
UM, IS IT USED
IN NEGATIVE WAYS ?  YEAH.

123
00:10:05,671 --> 00:10:08,173
BUT MY VIEW HAS ALWAYS BEEN...

124
00:10:08,174 --> 00:10:10,176
VISIBILITY AT ANY COST.

125
00:10:10,676 --> 00:10:14,179
UM, I'D RATHER HAVE NEGATIVE
THAN NOTHING.

126
00:10:14,180 --> 00:10:18,184
THAT'S JUST
MY PARTICULAR VIEW, AND ALSO 'CAUSE I AM A SISSY.

127
00:10:18,184 --> 00:10:21,687
♪ AND GO DASHING
UP AND DOWN THE HALL ♪

128
00:10:21,687 --> 00:10:24,189
[ Tomlin ]
IN ONE MOVIE YOU COULD EVEN FIND SISSIES TABLE-HOPPING...

129
00:10:24,190 --> 00:10:28,194
IN HOLLYWOOD'S FIRST PEEK
AT A GAY BAR.

130
00:10:28,194 --> 00:10:31,697
♪ IF A SAILOR IN PAJAMAS
I SHOULD SEE ♪

131
00:10:31,697 --> 00:10:35,701
♪ I KNOW HE'D SCARE
THE LIFE OUT OF ME ♪

132
00:10:35,701 --> 00:10:37,703
♪ AND ON A GREAT BIG
BATTLESHIP ♪

133
00:10:38,204 --> 00:10:40,706
♪ YOU'D LIKE TO BE ♪

134
00:10:40,706 --> 00:10:44,710
♪ WORKING AS CHAMBERMAIDS ♪
[ Patrons Laughing ]

135
00:10:44,710 --> 00:10:47,212
WELL, SISSY CHARACTERS
IN MOVIES...

136
00:10:47,213 --> 00:10:50,716
WERE ALWAYS A JOKE.

137
00:10:50,716 --> 00:10:54,219
THERE'S NO SIN
LIKE BEING A WOMAN.

138
00:10:54,220 --> 00:10:58,224
WHEN A MAN DRESSES AS A WOMAN,
THE AUDIENCE LAUGHS.

139
00:10:58,224 --> 00:11:01,227
WHEN A WOMAN DRESSES AS A MAN,
NOBODY LAUGHS.

140
00:11:01,627 --> 00:11:04,730
THEY JUST THOUGHT
SHE LOOKED WONDERFUL.

141
00:11:09,735 --> 00:11:13,238
[ Male Audience Exclaiming ]

142
00:11:19,245 --> 00:11:21,747
I SAW MARLENE DEITRICH
IN MOROCCO...

143
00:11:21,747 --> 00:11:25,250
WHEN I WAS A TEENAGER;
I JUST WAS FLIPPING THE CHANNELS AND SAW HER...

144
00:11:25,251 --> 00:11:28,254
AND DECIDED
TO SETTLE IN FOR AN OLD MOVIE.

145
00:11:28,254 --> 00:11:30,256
AND THERE'S
THIS SCENE...

146
00:11:30,256 --> 00:11:34,260
WHERE SHE COMES
INTO A NIGHTCLUB, AND SHE'S JUST STUNNING...

147
00:11:34,260 --> 00:11:36,262
IN THIS TUXEDO.

148
00:11:38,764 --> 00:11:41,767
MAY I HAVE THIS ?
OF COURSE !

149
00:11:46,272 --> 00:11:49,775
[ Everyone Laughs ]

150
00:11:53,279 --> 00:11:57,783
AND THE CAMERA LINGERS.  IT
WASN'T LIKE I WAS CATCHING THIS OUT OF THE SIDE OF THE SCREEN.

151
00:11:57,783 --> 00:11:59,785
IT'S RIGHT IN THE CENTER.

152
00:11:59,785 --> 00:12:02,287
SHE HAS A ROMANCE
WITH GARY COOPER IN THIS MOVIE,

153
00:12:02,288 --> 00:12:04,790
BUT THAT WENT RIGHT
OUT THE WINDOW FOR ME.

154
00:12:04,790 --> 00:12:07,793
I WAS JUST LIKE, WHO WAS THAT
WOMAN ?  WHAT HAD HAPPENED ?

155
00:12:07,793 --> 00:12:11,797
I STARTED WRITING
A WHOLE OTHER SCRIPT FOR WHAT WAS REALLY GOING ON.

156
00:12:11,797 --> 00:12:15,801
SO THE THING WORKED
FOR EVERYBODY OF EVERY SEX.

157
00:12:15,801 --> 00:12:20,305
AND WHAT'S AMAZING,
I DON'T THINK THEY'VE DONE ANYTHING...

158
00:12:20,306 --> 00:12:23,809
AS DELICIOUS SEXUALLY
AS THAT SINCE.

159
00:12:25,311 --> 00:12:27,813
THEY DIDN'T PRETEND IT WAS
ANYTHING BUT WHAT IT WAS:

160
00:12:27,813 --> 00:12:31,316
SHE WAS DOING IT TO TURN ON
BOTH THE WOMAN AND THE MAN,

161
00:12:31,317 --> 00:12:34,320
WHICH APPEALED TO EVERYBODY.

162
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:37,823
AS IT SHOULD.
IT WAS SO FREE.

163
00:12:43,329 --> 00:12:45,331
[ Woman ]
EBBA !  COME IN.

164
00:12:45,331 --> 00:12:47,333
[ Man ]
NOW DON'T DALLY, YOUR MAJESTY.

165
00:12:47,333 --> 00:12:49,335
YOU HAVE A BUSY DAY.

166
00:12:49,835 --> 00:12:52,337
MORNING, EBBA.

167
00:12:52,338 --> 00:12:54,840
WHAT ARE YOU DOING UP
SO EARLY ? I COULDN'T SLEEP.

168
00:12:54,840 --> 00:12:56,842
[ Tomlin ]
THE MOVIE QUEEN CHRISTINA...

169
00:12:56,842 --> 00:13:01,847
WAS BASED ON THE LIFE
OF A REAL SWEDISH MONARCH AND LESBIAN.

170
00:13:01,847 --> 00:13:03,849
HOLLYWOOD CHANGED THE STORY,

171
00:13:04,350 --> 00:13:06,352
BUT TRACES OF THE TRUTH
SEEMED TO LINGER.

172
00:13:06,352 --> 00:13:11,357
THERE ARE RUMORS
THAT YOUR MAJESTY IS PLANNING A FOREIGN MARRIAGE.

173
00:13:11,357 --> 00:13:13,359
THEY ARE BASELESS.

174
00:13:13,359 --> 00:13:15,861
BUT YOUR MAJESTY,

175
00:13:16,362 --> 00:13:19,865
YOU CANNOT DIE AN OLD MAID !

176
00:13:19,865 --> 00:13:22,868
I HAVE NO INTENTION TO,
CHANCELLOR.

177
00:13:22,868 --> 00:13:26,872
I SHALL DIE A BACHELOR !

178
00:13:26,872 --> 00:13:29,374
WE HOPE THAT IT
WILL NOT BE NECESSARY...

179
00:13:29,375 --> 00:13:31,877
TO CLOSE ALL
THE MOTION PICTURE HOUSES...

180
00:13:31,877 --> 00:13:35,380
BECAUSE OF SOME OF THE ONES
THAT ARE NOT DESIRABLE,

181
00:13:35,381 --> 00:13:38,884
BUT THAT WE WILL HAVE CLEANER
AND BETTER MOTION PICTURES,

182
00:13:39,385 --> 00:13:41,387
SO THAT THEY MAY ALL STAY OPEN.

183
00:13:51,897 --> 00:13:54,399
WHAT HAPPENED, OF COURSE,
IN THE '20s AND THE '30s...

184
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:56,402
WHEN THEY BEGAN TO GET
VERY RAUNCHY,

185
00:13:56,402 --> 00:14:00,406
THE CATHOLIC CHURCH AND
FUNDAMENTALIST PROTESTANTS...

186
00:14:00,406 --> 00:14:02,908
CAME DOWN HARD.

187
00:14:02,908 --> 00:14:04,910
YOU KNOW THERE WAS
A LOT OF PULPIT STUFF, A LOT OF PREACHING...

188
00:14:05,411 --> 00:14:09,915
ABOUT ORGIASTIC ASPECTS
OF WHAT WAS HAPPENING ON THE SCREEN.

189
00:14:13,419 --> 00:14:17,923
[ Man ]
THE BIG CHANGE OCCURRED WHEN THE MOVIE MOGULS GOT TOGETHER.

190
00:14:17,923 --> 00:14:19,925
"LET'S SAVE HOLLYWOOD.

191
00:14:19,925 --> 00:14:23,428
"WE MUST GET AN OUTSIDER,
PREFERABLY SOME POLITICIAN...

192
00:14:23,429 --> 00:14:26,432
WHO IS ABOVE SUSPICION."

193
00:14:26,432 --> 00:14:30,436
SO THEY LOOKED INTO THE CABINET
OF WARREN G. HARDING.

194
00:14:30,436 --> 00:14:34,440
AT THAT TIME THERE WERE A NUMBER
OF UNINDICTED MEMBERS OF HIS CABINET.

195
00:14:34,440 --> 00:14:37,943
AND THEY PICKED THE POSTMASTER
GENERAL, WILL HAYS OF INDIANA,

196
00:14:37,943 --> 00:14:41,446
WHO LOOKED
NOT UNLIKE MICKEY MOUSE.

197
00:14:41,447 --> 00:14:44,450
THE CODE SETS UP HIGH STANDARDS
OF PERFORMANCE...

198
00:14:44,950 --> 00:14:46,952
FOR MOTION PICTURE PRODUCERS.

199
00:14:46,952 --> 00:14:48,954
IT STATES THE CONSIDERATIONS...

200
00:14:48,954 --> 00:14:51,456
WHICH GOOD TASTE AND COMMUNITY
VALUE...

201
00:14:51,457 --> 00:14:55,961
MAKE NECESSARY IN THIS
UNIVERSAL FORM OF ENTERTAINMENT.

202
00:14:55,961 --> 00:15:00,465
[ Tomlin ]
WILL HAYS WOULD HEAD THE MOVIES' FIRST VOLUNTARY EFFORT...

203
00:15:00,466 --> 00:15:02,468
AT SELF-CENSORSHIP.

204
00:15:02,468 --> 00:15:06,472
THE EARLY HAYS CODE WAS A TOKEN
GESTURE, SELDOM TAKEN SERIOUSLY.

205
00:15:06,972 --> 00:15:10,475
BUT BY 1934 THE CATHOLIC CHURCH
HAD DEVISED...

206
00:15:10,476 --> 00:15:12,478
A SCHEME OF ITS OWN.

