OUTSIDE WEARING PERFUME, GARDENIA.

274
00:19:57,763 --> 00:20:02,267
AND THEN WE ALSO HEAR SOME KIND
OF FUNNY, SLIGHTLY ORIENTAL,

275
00:20:02,267 --> 00:20:05,270
FEMININE MUSIC.

276
00:20:05,270 --> 00:20:08,273
- WILL YOU SIT DOWN,
MR. CAIRO ? - THANK YOU, SIR.

277
00:20:08,273 --> 00:20:11,776
[ Tomlin ]
THE ORIGINAL NOVEL DIDN'T MINCE WORDS ABOUT LORRE'S CHARACTER.

278
00:20:11,777 --> 00:20:14,279
IT READ, THIS GUY IS QUEER.

279
00:20:14,279 --> 00:20:19,284
MAY I OFFER CONDOLENCES
FOR YOUR PARTNER'S UNFORTUNATE DEATH ?

280
00:20:19,284 --> 00:20:21,786
[ Tomlin ]
THE MOVIE COULD ONLY HINT-- BROADLY.

281
00:20:21,787 --> 00:20:26,291
SEE, MR. SPADE,
I'M TRYING TO RECOVER AN ORNAMENT...

282
00:20:26,291 --> 00:20:28,793
THAT, UH, SHALL WE SAY
HAS BEEN MISLAID ?

283
00:20:28,794 --> 00:20:31,797
UH-HUH.
I HOPED YOU COULD ASSIST ME.

284
00:20:31,797 --> 00:20:34,800
THE ORNAMENT IS A STATUETTE,

285
00:20:34,800 --> 00:20:37,302
A BLACK FIGURE OF A BIRD.

286
00:20:39,805 --> 00:20:41,807
[ Tomlin ]
LEAVE IT TO ALFRED HITCHCOCK TO CREATE...

287
00:20:41,807 --> 00:20:43,809
NOT ONE,
BUT TWO GAY VILLAINS.

288
00:20:43,809 --> 00:20:46,812
MURDEROUS LOVERS, BASED
ON REAL-LIFE PSYCHOPATHS...

289
00:20:46,812 --> 00:20:49,314
LEOPOLD AND LOEB.

290
00:20:49,314 --> 00:20:52,817
WE KNEW THAT THEY WERE GAY.
YEAH.  SURE.

291
00:20:52,818 --> 00:20:55,821
I MEAN, NOBODY SAID ANYTHING
ABOUT IT.

292
00:20:55,821 --> 00:20:59,324
THIS WAS 1947.
LET'S NOT FORGET THAT.

293
00:20:59,324 --> 00:21:02,327
<i>THAT WAS ONE OF THE--</i>

294
00:21:02,828 --> 00:21:04,830
<i>THE POINTS OF THE FILM,</i>
<i>IN A WAY.</i>

295
00:21:04,830 --> 00:21:06,832
BRANDON,
HOW DID YOU FEEL ?

296
00:21:06,832 --> 00:21:09,835
WHEN ?
DURING IT.

297
00:21:10,836 --> 00:21:13,338
I... DON'T KNOW, REALLY.

298
00:21:13,338 --> 00:21:16,841
I DON'T REMEMBER FEELING
VERY MUCH OF ANYTHING.

299
00:21:18,343 --> 00:21:22,347
UNTIL HIS BODY WENT LIMP.

300
00:21:22,347 --> 00:21:24,849
AND I KNEW IT WAS OVER.

301
00:21:24,850 --> 00:21:28,353
AND THEN ?
THEN I FELT...

302
00:21:28,353 --> 00:21:30,855
TREMENDOUSLY EXHILARATED.

303
00:21:31,356 --> 00:21:33,858
H-HOW DID YOU FEEL ?

304
00:21:33,859 --> 00:21:36,862
[ Laurents ]
I DON'T THINK THE CENSORS AT THAT TIME...

305
00:21:36,862 --> 00:21:40,365
REALIZED THAT THIS
WAS ABOUT GAY PEOPLE.

306
00:21:40,365 --> 00:21:44,869
THEY DIDN'T HAVE A CLUE
WHAT WAS AND WHAT WASN'T. THAT'S HOW IT GOT BY.

307
00:21:46,371 --> 00:21:48,373
[ Tomlin ]
SOMETIMES THE CENSORS TURNED A BLIND EYE...

308
00:21:48,373 --> 00:21:53,378
TO LESBIANS ON THE SCREEN
AS LONG AS THEY WERE KEPT SAFELY BEHIND BARS.

309
00:21:54,880 --> 00:21:56,882
HI, ANNE.
HELLO, HARPER.

310
00:21:57,382 --> 00:22:01,386
SINCE YOU WENT FANCY
WORKIN' FOR BENTON, I KIND OF MISSED YOU.

311
00:22:01,386 --> 00:22:05,390
THIS IS MARIE ALLEN.
